Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12:10:01 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=402.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My apologies</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First:<br>
My apologies to you Hagg, for not helping you to get to the cathedral last night. You know that I like you, and it wont hurt if I say it again; I like you Haggriden Lusarl! <br>
But on this one (going to the cathedral), I believe I'm helping you more by not helping you. I know that it may seem a little harsh, pusching the bird from the nest to see the eagle take it's flight. I want you to feel the pride of your completion. <br>
And congratulations once more for your level 30!! »APPLAUSE«<br>
<br>
Second:<br>
My apologies to Roy, for being witness of Dia's worst language. I was so mad!!! and I am ashamed today of what I have said. Here is the story;<br>
I was at the tent waiting for Celeroy when a little one came to me for help. He had a corpse in the lich room of the undead's dungeon near our tent, and , wasn't able to pick the lock to get to it. <br>
Of corse I went with him to help him out. I got him to the lich room and there, 3 guys where camping the place. One of them started to insult me; that I must be an idiot to be there at level 40 »» I answered that I was here to help (I dont remember the name, lets say X) »» He replied that it was dumm of me to open the door, to mind my own bussiness, that there were enough of them in that dungeon already. DOH!!<br>
My rage was coming, but that was not all....<br>
I asked X if that guy was one of his friends. »» Not really, he said, I just followed them in.<br>
I don't know exactly what was going on there, but I was shaking of rage. Being called an idiot by a guy that I believe was trying to steal an others corpse... I have vomit on him the worst words I could imagine, and wont repeat them anymore.<br>
In Dereth, I've seen the best, and now the worst.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>4:25:07 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=402.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My apologies</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Congrats on level 30 Harl!!! Good thing you had to take a month off, you would have passed us all by now!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Wow Dia, it's amazing how ignorant people can be. How does that saying go, no good deed goes unpunished? Bah. Just ignore them, they're not worth getting upset over. They looked like asses, but the young player you helped will admire you for a long time.<br>
<br>
Sorry I wasn't on last night, I couldn't get into the Zone all night for some reason. It was weird, on the boards I read some other people were having the same problem, but others weren't having trouble. I noticed they brought the worlds down today for maintanance, hopefully that fixed it.<br>
<br>
I doubt I'll be on much tonight though, I'm feeling pretty sick... ugh!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> </font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ulusarl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lusarl</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/19/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:57:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=402.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My apologies</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">First off I do not accept your appology Dia, for truly you have no reason to appologize. Your statements were correct and true no matter how harsh they appeared to others or you they simply shed light upon something I already knew in my heart. <br>
 Secondly I appologize, to all of you, for being as selfish as I was, Consistantly since I got back I have pestered each one of you to the fullest until I got you to come join me or take me someplace that you would not reagularly be.<br>
  I do not know why I forgot myself so or continued to press for assistance on things I really did not need help on. Perhaps it was the lack of companionship from you guys while I was away that created the desire to see you every moment you were on. I would like to say that it was an coniving attempt at catching up to you, (making you take me to a place you all got low exp and I got high exp) but I am not that smart. I do not know... But yes you were right. Perhaps Harl needs to take some time off and go hunting or exploring, or simply time to work on his personality a bit. To me being naked is sheer logic. It is more efficient. It saves an open spot, weighs less and since all my items use mana---saves mana stones. The same with running to a destination. I have not armored up for any run, other than the ones with you guys, since before I left for NE. Casting buffs is the same way, no sense in wasting comps on a spell that will wear out 2 mins into the fray just cuz I cast it to early. I know this sounds rude and I do not mean it to it is just my own personal strategy. Thus the same reason i have not gone exploring. If I am using mana then I might as well be getting loot not running to go somplace. These are the things that got me this high this fast. I also appologize for not being totaly honest. I know that I make you all a bit uncomfortable when I venture with you anywhere. The thought may not be more than a sliver but it is there in your minds every time I am around. Protect Harl.<br>
  I am thankful for this as it shows me just how much you guys do care but at the same time I suppose that lil things like that are my personal triunphs. being able to stand toe to toe with a lugian while wielding its mace against it, being able to run naked through the direlands dodging skeletal knights and shadows. Thankfully to all of you I have ner lost an item on ANY corpse. Now...I don't have to. I am old enough to get it back myself pretty much. But like I said Dia is right, Somewhere inside I long to do something of psuedo importance, something no one has done or something so strange it cannot be decipherd as madness or brilliance. I believe this is the same thing Crow longs for by switching to EQ, just on a larger scale. But is that not what these games are? A great distraction that gives a false sense of accomplishment? If one cannot accomplish anything in game then where can one do so? I have some things up my sleeve for AC, I just hope Crow gives me the opportunity to use it before he is gone from us. but until that day arrives I think Harl will be taking a short leave of absence to explore and find just what it is that will make him an individual and perhaps a bit special, in AC not just in the head. If you need me Just give me a tell I will always be up for a good grouping or simply to hunt. (I still owe Wamba some Metos time<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Till then Thank you for the light Dia and to the rest of you for the time<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
                         Haggriden Lusarl. <br>
